JOHANNESBURG – At least one expert says last week's hacking of financial services company Liberty, is a chance for South Africans to understand the worth of their personal information. The company announced on Saturday it had become the victim of hackers demanding a ransom not to release sensitive emails containing customers’ data. eNCA reporter Michael Appel spoke to an "ethical hacker" about the matter and about how South Africans can protect themselves. Watch the full report above. eNCA